{
  "stem": "8892.2",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And if he came home 12 o'clock before he opened the gate, because we had like a gate and a long yard, but the homes were close to each other, so it wasn't really a light where flowers could grow.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Further down, that's where they had flowers growing.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And that dog would be just outside, and going into the kitchen, to the house, we had five steps.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He would never cross the top steps.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "He would just lay on the top step but never get into the house.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So he was an outside dog, and he always slept in the barn-- winter, summer, that was his bed.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So my father wouldn't kill him, no way he'll kill.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "His name was Peszi.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He was a beautiful white dog with the brown spots.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that day Peszi stays, and my brother stays at the gate and watching this procedure, when going up they started at one end of the town where the family of the rabbis lived.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And they put him on a wagon, and we're already just approaching our wagon, and we see the wagon going by with all the rabbi's family.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Their name was [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the rabbi was an older rabbi but distinguished with the little-- not a long beard, just up to here-- and with a kittel, you know, the white kittel on, and a white yarmulke on.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "At that point, my brother saw this, he run to that, out of the thing.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "His door was-- I mean, the gate was open, and he's standing there and watching all this and stomaching it.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he run-- not our wagon, because we were not loaded yet, but the rabbi's wagon.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And just ran, jumped up the wagon and grabbed his hand and kissed them.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
